cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with the performance analysis of cognitive radio systems, which involves the use of information theory, networking, communication, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the power control mechanism and channel estimation, which are related to networking and communication, respectively. Hence, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the second likely category. The paper also focuses on the Underlay System (US) paradigm, which is a subcategory of cognitive radio systems, and hence, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the third likely category. The paper also proposes a novel model to capture the effect of channel estimation errors, which involves system modeling and analysis, and hence, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the maximum achievable throughput, which is related to multimedia systems, and hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is the fifth likely category.
